column6: Perfect quality of materials. No obstacles observed when processing or shipping to next checkpoint. Great.
Carried out perfectly. Faced errors in previous checkpoints which led to some hurdles in timing of release into market.
No problems in logistics. All materials have arrived without trouble. Passed.
Received materials with slight delay. No accidents during manufacturing stage. Passed onto next stage.
Approved materials for assembly. Few defects detected. Legitimacy is maintained with quality of products. Good to go for next step.
Batch tested and approved by quality check team. Little to no defects found. Negligible amounts of human error was found. Passed onto next stage.
Tested for quality of products one final time before packing the finished batch. Sent to shipping team.
Received all batches without any missing pieces. Sent out to shipping after logistics verifications. Perfect process and no error was made.
Recieved raw materials at factory. Logistics team had a delay of 3 days, which led to disruption in schedule. Sent to factory.
Received raw materials with poor quality and care taken to transport materials. Damaged goods were found while unpacking at factory. Passed onto next stage with a yellow flag.

Received warning of yellow flag. Team was only able to complete 70% of predicted quantity of products. This led to a delay in schedule to wait for new materials to arrive and complete the current batch. Passed onto the next batch with a delay of 5 days.
Quality was not the best condition. There were defective pieces found in the batch. They had to be scrapped or completely thrown out. Moved onto next stage.
Packaging team had to work Over Time to match with schedule since previous teams messed up with the schedule and process. Passed onto next stage on time.
Sent to shipment to distributors and retailers with a slight delay. Overall, it was not a productive batch.
